1
00:00:18,230 --> 00:00:20,350
[After a fierce competition,]

2
00:00:20,730 --> 00:00:22,380
[the 10 directors are entering Round 3]

3
00:00:23,230 --> 00:00:27,100
[The teaser mission that
captivated us for 90 seconds]

4
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:30,630
[They proved their talents in unique styles!]

5
00:00:31,340 --> 00:00:34,560
[The 90-second teasers are finally
being made into short dramas!]

6
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:38,110
[The last hurdle to the final]

7
00:00:38,110 --> 00:00:42,550
[The 1:1 death match that no one will back down]

8
00:00:42,910 --> 00:00:46,090
[You have to win to survive]

9
00:00:46,090 --> 00:00:48,240
It was easy to copy him.

10
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,970
It's not something you can just copy.

11
00:00:49,970 --> 00:00:51,550
I went all in.

12
00:00:51,550 --> 00:00:54,330
This will be your last time on stage.

13
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:56,800
It's going up that high?

14
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:58,520
That much?

15
00:00:58,520 --> 00:01:00,290
It was disappointing and chaotic.

16
00:01:00,290 --> 00:01:02,370
I think I was expecting too much.

17
00:01:02,370 --> 00:01:05,430
It didn't feel very new.

18
00:01:05,430 --> 00:01:07,420
The short drama viewers don't wait for you.

19
00:01:07,420 --> 00:01:09,880
I'm a bit flustered, to be honest.

20
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:11,800
[Impactful 180 seconds will
determine their fates!]

21
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:14,260
[What will happen in the death match round?]

22
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:18,050
[1:1 death match]

23
00:01:18,050 --> 00:01:20,350
[They bet it all on short drama to survive]

24
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:22,380
[The fate-determining]

25
00:01:22,380 --> 00:01:23,890
[1:1 death match]

26
00:01:23,890 --> 00:01:26,140
[The day of the battle]

27
00:01:26,410 --> 00:01:28,710
[Right before the taping started]

28
00:01:29,510 --> 00:01:32,110
[They are gathering in an unfamiliar space]

29
00:01:32,110 --> 00:01:34,010
Where are we?

30
00:01:34,820 --> 00:01:37,470
[Sitting with their death match opponents]

31
00:01:37,970 --> 00:01:40,810
[When the ten directors are here,]

32
00:01:40,810 --> 00:01:42,290
[the battle starts]

33
00:01:42,660 --> 00:01:44,310
[Very tense]

34
00:01:44,930 --> 00:01:47,090
[Director Lee Joo Seung is
the last one to arrive]

35
00:01:47,560 --> 00:01:49,130
[This is...]

36
00:01:49,850 --> 00:01:52,980
[the monitor room where they will
watch the short dramas together]

37
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:55,780
[Already very intense]

38
00:01:56,970 --> 00:01:58,980
[They're even breathing cautiously]

39
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:01,820
[Deep breaths]

40
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:04,100
Are you nervous, too, Yoo Jin?

41
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:05,480
- Yes.
- Are you nervous?

42
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:09,300
You don't seem nervous
because you've been doing this.

43
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:10,560
I am.

44
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:14,180
- Isn't everyone nervous?
- We all are, right?

45
00:02:14,180 --> 00:02:15,350
I want to use the bathroom.

46
00:02:15,350 --> 00:02:18,670
I can hear my heart beating
as I lean on this chair.

47
00:02:18,670 --> 00:02:20,770
Boom, boom, boom, boom.

48
00:02:22,830 --> 00:02:25,600
It was so nerve-racking, and it's 1:1.

49
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:30,310
My legs were shaky, and my heart was racing.

50
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:31,840
[His soul left his body]

51
00:02:33,110 --> 00:02:36,700
We are finally showing the actual series.

52
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:40,790
I was curious what they would think of it.

53
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,500
I think it will be a close battle.

54
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:47,490
It's so unpredictable.

55
00:02:47,490 --> 00:02:49,590
You don't know who will win.

56
00:02:49,590 --> 00:02:52,420
I'm certain that I'll win.

57
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:56,580
[Feeling nervous even before it starts]

58
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:58,960
[Meanwhile]

59
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,810
[People are entering the studio]

60
00:03:02,260 --> 00:03:04,220
[Familiar faces]

61
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:06,310
[Director Yeo Ha Ni / Director Kim Yi An]

62
00:03:06,310 --> 00:03:09,980
[Participating as viewers, not directors]

63
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:13,460
[Snacking before they start judging]

64
00:03:15,420 --> 00:03:19,680
[The atmosphere is tense, but the air is fresh]

65
00:03:20,390 --> 00:03:21,860
[Refreshing]

66
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:24,700
[Round 3 finally starts]

67
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:25,950
[Director Lee Beom Gyu / Director Ha Soo Ho]

68
00:03:27,580 --> 00:03:30,100
Finding the best short drama director in Korea.

69
00:03:30,100 --> 00:03:34,270
Korea's first short drama directing
competition, Director's Arena.

70
00:03:34,270 --> 00:03:38,540
Hello, I'm your dopamine navigator,
comedian Jang Do Yeon.

71
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:42,050
[Good to see you]

72
00:03:42,050 --> 00:03:44,560
After the cutthroat Round 2,

73
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:48,400
we're left with the last stage before the final.

74
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:52,060
There are ten surviving directors right now.

75
00:03:52,060 --> 00:03:56,430
But that number will be cut in half today.

76
00:03:56,430 --> 00:04:00,730
In Round 3, only one of the two survives.

77
00:04:00,730 --> 00:04:03,330
It's a 1:1 death match.

78
00:04:03,980 --> 00:04:06,300
- Oh, my God.
- I'm suddenly nervous.

79
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:08,870
I'm so nervous.

80
00:04:09,970 --> 00:04:15,730
These people's decisions will
determine the directors' fate today.

81
00:04:15,730 --> 00:04:19,830
Let me introduce you to the 50 viewers.

82
00:04:19,830 --> 00:04:21,500
[The short drama viewers]

83
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:23,290
[Familiar faces]

84
00:04:23,290 --> 00:04:25,340
[The directors join the panel]

85
00:04:25,340 --> 00:04:26,850
[We are in your care]

86
00:04:26,850 --> 00:04:28,820
Viewers.

87
00:04:28,820 --> 00:04:30,300
[Please]

88
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:34,030
Round 3's judging standards got even higher.

89
00:04:34,030 --> 00:04:36,480
It's because a new judge joined us.

90
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:39,320
The director of "Park Hwa-Young" and "Project Y."

91
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:41,560
Please welcome Director Lee Hwan.

92
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:45,390
[Welcome]

93
00:04:45,820 --> 00:04:48,670
[A powerful, realistic point of view]

94
00:04:48,670 --> 00:04:51,200
[Director Lee Hwan captures raw reality]

95
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:54,280
I've been watching the
short dramas from the show.

96
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:59,750
I thought short-form dramas
were all about dopamine,

97
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:03,510
but I'm learning that's not always the case.

98
00:05:03,510 --> 00:05:10,630
I am excited to see great short dramas today.

99
00:05:10,630 --> 00:05:12,960
[Excited about the judging]

100
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:15,730
Short drama directing
competition, Director's Arena.

101
00:05:15,730 --> 00:05:21,430
Dopamine-spiking dramas are waiting
for you in the death match round.

102
00:05:21,430 --> 00:05:26,020
You all remember the first 90-second
teaser mission, right?

103
00:05:26,020 --> 00:05:28,640
The short trailers got us curious.

104
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:32,520
We'll finally see the first and second episodes.

105
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,940
[They were powerful from the beginning]

106
00:05:35,390 --> 00:05:38,270
[But we'll no longer be teased]

107
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:41,110
[The 10 surviving directors' teasers]

108
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:43,820
[will turn into ten short dramas]

109
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,910
[More impactful]

110
00:05:45,910 --> 00:05:47,740
[More fun]

111
00:05:47,740 --> 00:05:49,320
[More engaging]

112
00:05:49,990 --> 00:05:52,400
[Welcome to the unstoppable
world of short dramas]

113
00:05:52,850 --> 00:05:58,410
Round 3 will also be judged with stop
votes that put everyone in fear.

114
00:05:58,410 --> 00:06:00,520
While watching the dramas,

115
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:02,810
and if you think it's no longer interesting,

116
00:06:02,810 --> 00:06:05,980
press the stop button without hesitating.

117
00:06:05,980 --> 00:06:08,630
Aren't we using the average
viewing time this time?

118
00:06:08,630 --> 00:06:10,130
We aren't using that.

119
00:06:10,130 --> 00:06:12,870
We are only checking the stop counts today.

120
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:16,800
But we, Five Stars, need to make
decisions carefully today.

121
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:20,100
- How come?
- Each viewer's vote counts as one point.

122
00:06:20,100 --> 00:06:22,440
But each of Five Stars' votes
will count as 10 points.

123
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:24,530
The maximum stop count is 100.

124
00:06:24,530 --> 00:06:26,610
You're eliminated if your stop count
is higher than your opponent's.

125
00:06:26,610 --> 00:06:28,910
If it's lower, you advance to the next round.

126
00:06:28,910 --> 00:06:32,880
If all Five Stars press the stop button,

127
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:36,200
it will be the same as when
all viewers press the button.

128
00:06:36,200 --> 00:06:37,430
[No way]

129
00:06:37,790 --> 00:06:38,980
What do we do?

130
00:06:38,980 --> 00:06:43,410
Getting a vote from a judge would be so damaging.

131
00:06:43,410 --> 00:06:45,040
I know.

132
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,630
[I want to go home...]

133
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:49,390
Even if you get more votes from the viewers,

134
00:06:49,390 --> 00:06:53,410
you could come from behind,
depending on the Five Stars' decisions.

135
00:06:53,410 --> 00:06:56,990
This is your first time judging,
Director Lee Hwan.

136
00:06:56,990 --> 00:06:59,030
I'm curious to hear about your judging standards.

137
00:06:59,030 --> 00:07:02,330
I would prioritize what's most entertaining.

138
00:07:02,330 --> 00:07:07,460
The second most important thing
is the director's message.

139
00:07:07,460 --> 00:07:09,070
I'll try to follow the pacing.

140
00:07:09,070 --> 00:07:10,840
I'll turn it off if I'm bored in ten seconds.

141
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,550
How scary.

142
00:07:12,550 --> 00:07:14,640
That's how short dramas are.

143
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,880
I won't judge based on the technicalities.

144
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:19,410
- If I don't find it entertaining...
- That's the best way.

145
00:07:19,410 --> 00:07:22,720
I'll press it if the flow gets cut off.

146
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:27,750
That means he'll follow his instincts.

147
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:30,610
Only one survives in the 1:1 death match.

148
00:07:30,610 --> 00:07:32,370
We'll start the battle now.

149
00:07:32,370 --> 00:07:34,990
It's short drama time.

150
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:39,820
[It's finally battle time]

151
00:07:39,820 --> 00:07:41,840
My heart... Gosh.

152
00:07:41,840 --> 00:07:43,210
I hope it's not us.

153
00:07:43,210 --> 00:07:45,440
- I want to go later.
- Me, too.

154
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:47,750
[Who will go first?]

155
00:07:47,750 --> 00:07:50,960
It may be a death match, but we're
starting out with beauties.

156
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:54,070
It's a battle between two beautiful directors.

157
00:07:55,910 --> 00:07:58,720
[Yang Gyeong Hee vs. Park So Rang]

158
00:08:00,910 --> 00:08:04,620
They call me the Bong Joon Ho of the BL genre.

159
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:08,430
I gained many fans by ranking No. 1.

160
00:08:08,430 --> 00:08:10,720
[Time slip rom-com, "Joseon Man, MZ Woman"]

161
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:14,040
A certain level of quality is guaranteed.

162
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:17,350
The No. 1 short drama director, Park So Rang.

163
00:08:17,350 --> 00:08:18,840
[Impressive]

164
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:21,770
[The intense adult romance]

165
00:08:21,770 --> 00:08:23,990
That was dopamine itself.

166
00:08:23,990 --> 00:08:28,070
It shows how a short drama should be.

167
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:30,120
[But]

168
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:33,670
I'm not sure if it was the acting or directing.

169
00:08:33,670 --> 00:08:35,810
It was so disappointing.

170
00:08:35,810 --> 00:08:39,200
It made me reflect as a director.

171
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:44,450
I wish you had made it
a little bit more realistic.

172
00:08:44,450 --> 00:08:48,300
It's like well-made seaweed soup
without sesame oil.

173
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,770
It was a bit disappointing.

174
00:08:49,770 --> 00:08:52,430
I'll show you a ton of sesame oil.

175
00:08:52,430 --> 00:08:55,020
[They came determined for the Round 3 battle]

176
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:58,710
[What will happen to the two directors?]

177
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:02,400
I don't think I got to prove myself.

178
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,950
Round 2 was a team mission.

179
00:09:04,950 --> 00:09:08,700
I came determined to prove
myself properly this time.

180
00:09:10,330 --> 00:09:11,770
This is a short drama competition.

181
00:09:11,770 --> 00:09:14,240
"This is how a short drama is done."

182
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:16,130
I think they'll say that.

183
00:09:16,130 --> 00:09:19,700
That's what I think I achieved this time.

184
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:23,060
Your ranks are neck and neck right now.

185
00:09:23,060 --> 00:09:24,220
In Round 1,

186
00:09:24,220 --> 00:09:27,220
Director Park was in 7th place,
and Director Yang was in 8th place.

187
00:09:27,220 --> 00:09:31,000
In Round 2, Director Park was in 4th place.

188
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,830
And Director Yang was in 5th place.

189
00:09:33,830 --> 00:09:37,540
Director Park was always ahead in rank.

190
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:41,530
Director Yang, do you think
you could win this time?

191
00:09:41,530 --> 00:09:44,300
I wanted you to stick around for a long time.

192
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:46,860
But this will be your last time on stage.

193
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:47,860
Wow.

194
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:50,340
- This is more fun than a short drama.
- It's like "Show Me the Money."

195
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:51,970
This should be turned into a short drama.

196
00:09:51,970 --> 00:09:53,140
It's hip-hop style.

197
00:09:53,140 --> 00:09:55,980
I told her in the last round.

198
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:59,070
I said I'll prove why I'm the
No. 1 short-drama director.

199
00:09:59,070 --> 00:10:00,700
She'll get to see why today.

200
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:03,420
[Sweet yet brutal women's power]

201
00:10:03,420 --> 00:10:06,460
The first battle is already exciting.

202
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:09,100
We'll start the death match now.

203
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:12,350
Wait in the waiting area if you are going second.

204
00:10:12,350 --> 00:10:15,320
Director Yang Gyeong Hee directed

205
00:10:15,320 --> 00:10:17,310
"Joseon Man, MZ Woman."

206
00:10:17,310 --> 00:10:20,140
And it says "And a gay man" at the bottom.

207
00:10:20,810 --> 00:10:22,370
And a gay man.

208
00:10:22,370 --> 00:10:25,320
- That wasn't a part of it before.
- That sounds fun.

209
00:10:25,320 --> 00:10:27,370
She's adding more dopamine.

210
00:10:27,370 --> 00:10:30,870
In Round 1, Mr. Cha Tae Hyun

211
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:33,840
mentioned that I'm the Bong Joon Ho of BL.

212
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:37,740
I tried to reflect that by changing the script.

213
00:10:37,740 --> 00:10:41,370
I tried toning things up a little.

214
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:44,530
[Director Yang Gyeong Hee's short drama set]

215
00:10:44,530 --> 00:10:46,520
[Joseon's king is time-traveling to Hongdae]

216
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:48,110
[He's about to land here]

217
00:10:48,110 --> 00:10:51,280
It's about Joseon's King Lee Hyeon
ending up in Hongdae

218
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:54,870
and things happen while living with an MZ woman.

219
00:10:54,870 --> 00:11:01,780
I'm actress Jeong Gu Hyeon,
who's playing an MZ-er, Min Ji.

220
00:11:01,780 --> 00:11:03,910
Something to brag about myself?

221
00:11:03,910 --> 00:11:05,120
Well...

222
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:09,010
It might not be necessary to brag.

223
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:10,990
[I just live life on my own terms!]

224
00:11:10,990 --> 00:11:13,560
[The old-fashioned king of Joseon is
paired up with an MZ-er]

225
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:15,580
[Explosive looks]

226
00:11:15,580 --> 00:11:17,820
[And a nice voice on top of that]

227
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:19,970
[Actor Park Tae Rin]

228
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:22,960
[Director Yang is giving directions
from the second floor]

229
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:25,750
[Lee Hyeon and Min Ji are running at full speed]

230
00:11:26,710 --> 00:11:28,890
[A chase scene in the middle of the city?]

231
00:11:29,810 --> 00:11:35,370
Because Lee Hyeon looks exactly
like a top actor, Lee Do Yun,

232
00:11:35,370 --> 00:11:38,640
he's chased by his fans in Episode 2.

233
00:11:40,090 --> 00:11:42,220
[But]

234
00:11:42,510 --> 00:11:46,140
[A new character stands out]

235
00:11:47,370 --> 00:11:51,470
I'm actor Jeong Ho Gyun,
and I play Kim Ddol Ddol.

236
00:11:51,470 --> 00:11:56,930
I play a feminine male character
on social media these days.

237
00:11:56,930 --> 00:12:02,230
[Actor Jeong Ho Gyun with boyish
charm and sensitive qualities]

238
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:05,340
My left profile is better. You'll get
a better shot from here.

239
00:12:05,340 --> 00:12:07,210
[Asking to move the camera]

240
00:12:07,210 --> 00:12:08,760
I'll move it for you.

241
00:12:09,430 --> 00:12:11,270
You're definitely a character.

242
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:15,180
I added a gay character named Kim Ddol Ddol.

243
00:12:15,180 --> 00:12:18,360
I thought I should refresh things
with an additional character.

244
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:20,510
I was hoping to add a character

245
00:12:20,510 --> 00:12:23,710
that reflects the open-mindedness of our time.

246
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:27,970
That's how I naturally ended up
adding a gay character.

247
00:12:27,970 --> 00:12:29,540
Kim Ddol Ddol is so funny.

248
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:33,600
I thought a lot about how
to make this character shine.

249
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:35,690
I hope you find it entertaining.

250
00:12:35,690 --> 00:12:38,920
[A highlight of Kim Ddol Ddol]

251
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:41,510
Cut!

252
00:12:42,210 --> 00:12:46,500
Cut! Cut! Cut! Cut!

253
00:12:46,500 --> 00:12:49,810
[Kim Ddol Ddol's unstoppable passion]

254
00:12:50,820 --> 00:12:51,820
[Provocative]

255
00:12:51,820 --> 00:12:53,350
No, no, no.

256
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:57,590
I'm sorry. It's my character.

257
00:12:57,590 --> 00:13:02,810
[Can this interesting character get her to win?]

258
00:13:03,570 --> 00:13:05,420
Please tell us what to focus on.

259
00:13:05,420 --> 00:13:08,900
Since my drama has strong characters,

260
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:11,730
you'll be able to understand them right away.

261
00:13:11,730 --> 00:13:13,480
I hope you enjoy the scenes

262
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:18,230
and just have fun without thinking too much.

263
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:21,410
Sounds good. We'll start the judging now.

264
00:13:21,410 --> 00:13:24,160
[The judge's stop count will
be revealed at the end]

265
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:27,120
- It's playing.
- Wow.

266
00:13:27,710 --> 00:13:30,470
[Everyone is curious about the first one]

267
00:13:30,820 --> 00:13:32,430
[Her competition is getting ready, too]

268
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:37,010
[The first voting is always unpredictable]

269
00:13:37,490 --> 00:13:40,780
I'm worried that the genre will be too decisive.

270
00:13:40,780 --> 00:13:44,860
Rom-com and comedy tend to
follow people's preferences.

271
00:13:44,860 --> 00:13:48,670
I think that will divide people up a lot.

272
00:13:48,670 --> 00:13:52,090
["Joseon Man, MZ Woman, and a Gay Man"]

273
00:13:52,090 --> 00:13:55,230
Is Joseon's King Lee Hyeon dying like this?

274
00:13:55,230 --> 00:13:57,260
A new traditional tavern just opened.

275
00:13:57,260 --> 00:13:58,390
You can hook up.

276
00:13:58,390 --> 00:14:01,760
Could a chunk of gold fall from the sky?

277
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:04,090
What the f***?

278
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,220
Is this the afterlife?

279
00:14:11,970 --> 00:14:15,150
Who's this pervert?

280
00:14:15,780 --> 00:14:17,970
[Already got a stop vote?]

281
00:14:17,970 --> 00:14:19,830
Out on the streets?

282
00:14:21,230 --> 00:14:25,260
How dare you! I am Joseon's King Lee Hyeon.

283
00:14:25,260 --> 00:14:26,940
Done for the day.

284
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:30,500
Are you taking over my shift?

285
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:31,810
I'm leaving.

286
00:14:31,810 --> 00:14:32,810
[Joseon Tavern]

287
00:14:32,810 --> 00:14:33,940
Fighting.

288
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:35,650
What are you doing...

289
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:41,280
How could a woman take her
clothes off out on the streets?

290
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:44,640
[The stop count is skyrocketing]

291
00:14:45,430 --> 00:14:46,970
It's him.

292
00:14:46,970 --> 00:14:49,050
[Funny character]

293
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:55,000
Hey, bitch. Who's this man?

294
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:58,880
- Hello.
- You are Ddol Ddol, my trusty servant.

295
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:02,830
I named you Ddol Ddol because you are clever.

296
00:15:02,830 --> 00:15:04,830
Why does he keep calling me Ddol Ddol?

297
00:15:04,830 --> 00:15:08,800
[The stop count stopped after Ddol Ddol appeared]

298
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,400
Is he my ex-boyfriend?

299
00:15:10,460 --> 00:15:12,510
- Let's go.
- Hold on.

300
00:15:12,510 --> 00:15:14,190
He looks very familiar.

301
00:15:14,190 --> 00:15:15,530
Is he my ex-boyfriend?

302
00:15:15,530 --> 00:15:18,110
Show me your face, I said.

303
00:15:23,550 --> 00:15:26,120
It's Lee Do Yun!

304
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:28,710
Crazy! Lee Do Yun of "Star Embracing the Sun"?

305
00:15:28,710 --> 00:15:31,010
Run!

306
00:15:31,010 --> 00:15:32,860
I am Lee Hyeon, the king of Joseon.

307
00:15:32,860 --> 00:15:35,060
I do not know how I ended up here,

308
00:15:35,060 --> 00:15:37,900
but I am being chased by the people right now.

309
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:40,240
- It's Lee Do Yun!
- I am King Lee Hyeon of Joseon.

310
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:42,220
Why are they calling me Lee Do Yun?

311
00:15:42,220 --> 00:15:43,990
Geez, what the f***?

312
00:15:43,990 --> 00:15:46,860
What's with these bitches?

313
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:48,740
Get out of the way!

314
00:15:49,730 --> 00:15:51,440
He's mine!

315
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:53,740
At this very strange place,

316
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:55,740
I am being chased by the people.

317
00:15:55,740 --> 00:15:57,850
Oppa! Oppa! Oppa!

318
00:15:57,850 --> 00:16:01,550
[The two directors' mysterious expressions]

319
00:16:01,550 --> 00:16:03,570
[The smiles are gone]

320
00:16:03,570 --> 00:16:06,110
[The stop count is already over 20]

321
00:16:06,110 --> 00:16:07,130
[Anxious]

322
00:16:07,130 --> 00:16:09,110
It started going up rapidly.

323
00:16:09,110 --> 00:16:11,480
I thought, "This is no good."

324
00:16:12,150 --> 00:16:17,170
[The viewers' stop count alone
won't determine their fate]

325
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,760
I am being chased by the people.

326
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:23,670
Oppa! Oppa! Oppa!

327
00:16:26,010 --> 00:16:27,650
What's with those people?

328
00:16:27,650 --> 00:16:29,960
It's all your fault. Why did you say that name?

329
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:31,560
It's Lee Do Yun!

330
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:33,850
Lee Do Yun of "Star Embracing the Sun"!

331
00:16:33,850 --> 00:16:35,360
Oppa.

332
00:16:38,380 --> 00:16:40,990
I put dibs on him first, bitch.

333
00:16:52,170 --> 00:16:55,470
My gosh. My gosh. My gosh.

334
00:16:55,470 --> 00:16:57,460
Oh, no!

335
00:16:57,460 --> 00:16:59,460
[Funny]

336
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,260
Hurry!

337
00:17:16,390 --> 00:17:20,470
Oppa! Oppa! Oppa!

338
00:17:20,470 --> 00:17:22,370
Where did these bastards go?

339
00:17:22,370 --> 00:17:25,740
I'm not Lee Do Yun!

340
00:17:27,070 --> 00:17:28,860
Who are those women?

341
00:17:28,860 --> 00:17:31,060
Why are they chasing me?

342
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:46,610
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

343
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:50,870
[Forcing a smile...]

344
00:17:50,870 --> 00:17:55,410
Director Yang Gyeong Hee's video ended.

345
00:17:55,410 --> 00:17:59,820
The stop count from the viewers is 27.

346
00:17:59,820 --> 00:18:01,550
[It's more than expected]

347
00:18:02,340 --> 00:18:04,770
I was like, "What do I do?"

348
00:18:04,770 --> 00:18:07,620
It was completely unexpected.

349
00:18:07,620 --> 00:18:10,470
[Time for Five Stars to start critiquing]

350
00:18:10,470 --> 00:18:13,460
It felt very dynamic.

351
00:18:13,460 --> 00:18:16,590
The editing was very speedy from the beginning.

352
00:18:16,590 --> 00:18:18,310
Hook, turn, cut.

353
00:18:18,310 --> 00:18:20,380
In my opinion,

354
00:18:20,380 --> 00:18:26,250
there were a lot of engaging shots.

355
00:18:27,060 --> 00:18:30,030
- That gay character...
- Ddol Ddol?

356
00:18:30,030 --> 00:18:32,790
When Ddol Ddol and the woman...

357
00:18:32,790 --> 00:18:35,540
- kissed...
- What suddenly happened?

358
00:18:35,540 --> 00:18:37,410
He must've hated it so much.

359
00:18:37,410 --> 00:18:39,940
[Why should he worry?]

360
00:18:42,020 --> 00:18:44,890
It was fun. Moments like that are important.

361
00:18:44,890 --> 00:18:50,470
Something kept happening whenever
I was about to push the button.

362
00:18:50,470 --> 00:18:51,590
I think it was done cleverly.

363
00:18:51,590 --> 00:18:53,330
What did you think, Director Lee Byeong Heon?

364
00:18:53,330 --> 00:18:56,510
I thought it was a close call, to be honest.

365
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:57,980
Episode 2 played,

366
00:18:57,980 --> 00:19:02,330
but the pacing was still like a teaser.

367
00:19:02,330 --> 00:19:06,980
I was hoping it would stop, but it won't.

368
00:19:06,980 --> 00:19:11,050
I kept wondering if I should push or not.

369
00:19:11,050 --> 00:19:13,040
[Did Director Lee Byeong Heon push the button?]

370
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:15,860
The three minutes felt very long to me.

371
00:19:15,860 --> 00:19:20,480
Things need to keep happening
in different sequences,

372
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:22,620
but it was just one event.

373
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:25,190
The three minutes felt so long.

374
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:31,680
Round 3, a death match between
Yang Gyeong Hee and Park So Rang.

375
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:36,650
Director Yang got 27 stops from the viewers.

376
00:19:36,650 --> 00:19:37,840
What do you think?

377
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:40,750
It was more than 50%.

378
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:42,990
I feel a little hurt.

379
00:19:42,990 --> 00:19:47,090
But that's not the final score.
It doesn't reflect our votes.

380
00:19:47,090 --> 00:19:49,480
[The judges' votes are yet to be revealed[

381
00:19:49,850 --> 00:19:52,350
[Director Park So Rang's judging starts]

382
00:19:53,980 --> 00:19:58,570
Director Park, you must have
watched everything in the back.

383
00:19:58,570 --> 00:20:01,510
What did you think of
Director Yang's short drama?

384
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:04,060
Director Yang's work and mine

385
00:20:04,060 --> 00:20:07,520
are so different in terms of genre and style.

386
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:12,310
I'm a little worried because it will
be a matter of difference in taste.

387
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:14,130
You can tell just from the thumbnails.

388
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:17,860
The color tones and the
feelings are very different.

389
00:20:17,860 --> 00:20:20,000
It's making me more curious.

390
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,510
It's Kim Kyu Jong.

391
00:20:21,510 --> 00:20:23,360
I see someone familiar up there.

392
00:20:23,360 --> 00:20:26,990
- SS501's Kim Kyu Jong, right?
- You're right.

393
00:20:26,990 --> 00:20:28,410
You must have a personal connection.

394
00:20:28,410 --> 00:20:29,820
[Happy to see him]

395
00:20:29,820 --> 00:20:31,360
I'm curious.

396
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:32,580
You don't know, right?

397
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:33,820
No.

398
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:38,200
This is like my hidden card.

399
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:43,460
I cast the actors you don't
often see in short dramas.

400
00:20:43,460 --> 00:20:45,720
I hope you're looking forward to it.

401
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:48,070
[More nervous than excited]

402
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,080
[Director Park So Rang's short drama set]

403
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:57,030
[Flashy wedding dress and various accessories]

404
00:20:57,030 --> 00:21:02,170
Which one of these has a fuller A-line?

405
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:05,190
[Checking all the dress details]

406
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:08,070
Costume is very important in short dramas.

407
00:21:08,070 --> 00:21:13,610
You can compose a shot a lot
more in a landscape format.

408
00:21:13,610 --> 00:21:15,520
But the landscape format is narrow.

409
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:20,540
The viewers naturally focus on the costumes.

410
00:21:20,540 --> 00:21:24,760
That's why costumes are
so important in short dramas.

411
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:27,950
[Eye-catching costumes]

412
00:21:27,950 --> 00:21:31,110
Getting you hooked in the beginning is crucial.

413
00:21:31,110 --> 00:21:35,520
Kiss for about three seconds.

414
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:38,350
[Starting with a hook-in point]

415
00:21:38,350 --> 00:21:41,190
I think I can separate myself from

416
00:21:41,190 --> 00:21:45,420
the inexperienced short-drama
directors with that.

417
00:21:45,420 --> 00:21:47,300
[Strategic scene placements]

418
00:21:47,730 --> 00:21:49,800
[The male lead is here]

419
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:51,960
[Kim Kyu Jong as Ji Han]

420
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:56,680
I've never felt so pressured on set.

421
00:21:56,680 --> 00:21:59,960
I didn't know it was part of a mission.

422
00:21:59,960 --> 00:22:04,220
It's so fun. I hope we do a good job
and get to film the whole thing.

423
00:22:05,130 --> 00:22:09,930
We got an amazing actor whom
you'd never see in short dramas.

424
00:22:09,930 --> 00:22:11,960
[The hottest actor of the moment!]

425
00:22:12,560 --> 00:22:14,550
[Hyun Bong Sik as Deok Ho]

426
00:22:14,550 --> 00:22:18,710
[His filmography ranges from comedy to drama]

427
00:22:19,050 --> 00:22:21,810
[They're playing brothers from a chaebol family]

428
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:25,260
[Explaining the context in detail]

429
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:28,470
[Clear directions]

430
00:22:28,710 --> 00:22:30,670
It's over. I'll be winning.

431
00:22:30,670 --> 00:22:33,060
I have these two actors.

432
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:35,000
What more can I say?

433
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,350
[Using a solid cast for the competition]

434
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:40,300
As for my main focus...

435
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,400
In the last mission,

436
00:22:42,400 --> 00:22:46,290
our work was called "seaweed soup
without sesame oil."

437
00:22:46,290 --> 00:22:49,950
It's like well-made seaweed soup
without sesame oil.

438
00:22:49,950 --> 00:22:51,900
I found that very hurtful.

439
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:57,120
I decided to add plenty of sesame oil this time.

440
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:58,210
Who made that comment?

441
00:22:58,210 --> 00:23:00,490
Doesn't that sound like director Lee Byeong Heon?

442
00:23:00,490 --> 00:23:01,890
I don't say stuff like that.

443
00:23:01,890 --> 00:23:03,830
It was Jang Keun Suk, as I remember.

444
00:23:03,830 --> 00:23:06,280
It was you, punk.

445
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:07,960
I don't say stuff like that.

446
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:10,430
I thought it sounded familiar.

447
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:12,520
It turns out I'm the one who said it.

448
00:23:12,520 --> 00:23:14,760
She made it nutty just for you.

449
00:23:14,760 --> 00:23:17,010
I feel like it was made just for me.

450
00:23:17,010 --> 00:23:18,570
All right.

451
00:23:19,270 --> 00:23:21,010
[Park So Rang's "Is This Marriage Valid?"]

452
00:23:23,100 --> 00:23:24,760
I was the second person to go.

453
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:29,820
I already know how many votes
Director Yang got from the viewers.

454
00:23:29,820 --> 00:23:31,970
I was so nervous.

455
00:23:34,580 --> 00:23:37,240
["Is This Marriage Valid?"]

456
00:23:38,040 --> 00:23:40,100
Gosh, my goodness.

457
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:41,990
From the very beginning.

458
00:23:41,990 --> 00:23:43,730
[Successful hook]

459
00:23:43,730 --> 00:23:45,590
[It's powerful]

460
00:23:46,580 --> 00:23:47,980
I'm screwed.

461
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:52,720
[Park So Rang's
"Is This Marriage Valid?" Episode 1]

462
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:55,830
I can't control myself. How can I with you?

463
00:23:57,680 --> 00:24:00,050
Can you do this when you're about to get married?

464
00:24:00,660 --> 00:24:02,450
Marriage is a formality.

465
00:24:02,450 --> 00:24:04,300
I'll reserve my love for you.

466
00:24:09,140 --> 00:24:11,420
Read the room, Lee Ye Na.

467
00:24:14,610 --> 00:24:15,630
[Sucked in]

468
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,490
Unni.

469
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:37,440
Ri Ah...

470
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:40,920
How did you come all the way here?

471
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:42,130
Surprise.

472
00:24:42,130 --> 00:24:44,420
She couldn't have missed her sister's wedding.

473
00:24:44,420 --> 00:24:46,140
I persuaded the doctor.

474
00:24:46,140 --> 00:24:48,150
This is all thanks to Se Ra.

475
00:24:48,150 --> 00:24:49,230
Se Ra.

476
00:24:49,230 --> 00:24:51,740
I gave you a proper wedding gift, okay?

477
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:54,580
This is the most valuable gift. Thank you.

478
00:24:54,580 --> 00:24:57,910
I'm so happy you are marrying a good person.

479
00:24:57,910 --> 00:25:00,150
My condition improved a lot
using the private room,

480
00:25:00,150 --> 00:25:01,720
thanks to our adoptive parents.

481
00:25:01,720 --> 00:25:03,300
What a relief.

482
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:07,820
This is the only way to repay my parents.

483
00:25:07,820 --> 00:25:11,180
If they didn't adopt me...

484
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:20,340
Congrats, my friend Ye Na.

485
00:25:21,120 --> 00:25:23,030
I was supposed to be in your position.

486
00:25:23,030 --> 00:25:25,900
That means I can ruin things, right?

487
00:25:27,350 --> 00:25:30,550
I was like, "Please don't press it.
Don't press it"

488
00:25:31,430 --> 00:25:33,980
It felt like my blood was drying up.

489
00:25:34,570 --> 00:25:37,550
The stop count was all I could see.

490
00:25:37,550 --> 00:25:39,650
[Yang Gyeong Hee got 18 stops
at the end of Episode 1]

491
00:25:39,650 --> 00:25:41,700
[Park So Rang has half of that so far]

492
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:43,710
[A 9-stop difference in Episode 1]

493
00:25:43,710 --> 00:25:48,560
[Park So Rang's
"Is This Marriage Valid?" Episode 2]

494
00:25:52,130 --> 00:25:54,090
Hey, brother.

495
00:25:55,250 --> 00:25:57,700
My little brother is back.
Let me see your handsome face.

496
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:59,630
Wow.

497
00:25:59,630 --> 00:26:01,930
- Bong Sik.
- It's Bong Sik.

498
00:26:02,830 --> 00:26:04,830
[Her hidden card]

499
00:26:04,830 --> 00:26:07,210
Hey, brother.

500
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:10,750
My little brother is back.
Let me see your handsome face.

501
00:26:10,750 --> 00:26:12,110
Why bother with an installation ceremony?

502
00:26:12,110 --> 00:26:13,750
We should just have a family dinner.

503
00:26:13,750 --> 00:26:15,280
It's about time you got married.

504
00:26:15,280 --> 00:26:18,140
Look for your future wife at the party tonight.

505
00:26:18,140 --> 00:26:20,230
It was Father's idea, wasn't it?

506
00:26:22,390 --> 00:26:24,840
Please welcome the bride.

507
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:30,720
How can I control myself with you?

508
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:32,730
Marriage is a formality.

509
00:26:32,730 --> 00:26:34,400
I'll reserve my love for you.

510
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:38,360
I-I'm sorry, Tae Ju.

511
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:40,570
Did you forget who I am?

512
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:53,360
Read the room, Lee Ye Na.

513
00:26:56,890 --> 00:26:59,870
But this is...

514
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:05,620
I told you not to cry.

515
00:27:05,620 --> 00:27:09,400
How many times did I tell you not to frown?

516
00:27:10,470 --> 00:27:11,310
What are you doing?

517
00:27:11,310 --> 00:27:13,870
I was able to endure your abuse.

518
00:27:13,870 --> 00:27:14,900
What?

519
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:19,400
I'm sorry, Mom and Dad.

520
00:27:22,500 --> 00:27:28,070
This marriage is annulled.

521
00:27:29,740 --> 00:27:31,620
Huh? It's over.

522
00:27:32,470 --> 00:27:35,070
So fun. She did a great job.

523
00:27:35,070 --> 00:27:37,470
This is what short dramas are.

524
00:27:37,470 --> 00:27:40,130
It ended all of a sudden.

525
00:27:40,130 --> 00:27:41,930
It kept giving me the chills.

526
00:27:41,930 --> 00:27:44,290
It's what you see in short dramas.

527
00:27:44,290 --> 00:27:47,450
I thought it was boring because
it's filled with clichés.

528
00:27:47,450 --> 00:27:51,920
But that could work with the viewers.

529
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:54,920
[Mixed opinions from the directors]

530
00:27:54,920 --> 00:27:57,530
[Can a cliché win?]

531
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:00,750
I tried so hard to keep a straight face.

532
00:28:00,750 --> 00:28:02,670
I thought I might be losing.

533
00:28:03,670 --> 00:28:08,660
The stop count is 13.

534
00:28:08,660 --> 00:28:12,120
I'm curious what the Five Stars thought.

535
00:28:13,010 --> 00:28:15,160
It definitely has sesame oil in it.

536
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:16,690
I definitely sensed it.

537
00:28:16,690 --> 00:28:18,730
- Was it nutty?
- It sure was.

538
00:28:18,730 --> 00:28:21,020
The intensity kept me hooked.

539
00:28:21,020 --> 00:28:25,560
I think it had all the elements
needed in a short drama.

540
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:28,510
I haven't had a dopamine rush
like this in a while.

541
00:28:29,850 --> 00:28:33,730
I realize what a short drama should be like.

542
00:28:33,730 --> 00:28:36,400
I couldn't look away from the screen.

543
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:39,190
I caught myself saying, "What a bastard."

544
00:28:39,190 --> 00:28:40,190
Me, too. Me, too.

545
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:43,270
That's what you were mumbling under your breath.

546
00:28:43,270 --> 00:28:44,480
That's it.

547
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:47,450
Right. From the beginning.

548
00:28:47,450 --> 00:28:49,940
Huh? They're cheating. Gosh.

549
00:28:50,930 --> 00:28:52,740
[A housewife watching a soap opera]

550
00:28:52,740 --> 00:28:54,100
What a bastard.

551
00:28:54,740 --> 00:28:59,150
It's fun to swear at someone who is pure evil.

552
00:28:59,150 --> 00:29:02,070
This is how it is, huh?

553
00:29:02,070 --> 00:29:05,070
You are a master at portraying passion.

554
00:29:05,070 --> 00:29:06,110
She's really good.

555
00:29:06,110 --> 00:29:09,360
You're like a short drama technician.

556
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:14,200
It's a stereotypical short drama,
and that's why I liked it.

557
00:29:14,210 --> 00:29:17,830
I was like, "This is it.
This is how you enjoy these."

558
00:29:17,830 --> 00:29:21,890
I heard a lot of the lines this time.

559
00:29:21,890 --> 00:29:26,130
I like that very much. I enjoyed it a lot.

560
00:29:26,130 --> 00:29:27,910
Huh? Are you...

561
00:29:28,830 --> 00:29:30,350
You're tearing up.

562
00:29:30,350 --> 00:29:32,400
I'm sorry. Should I try that again?

563
00:29:33,400 --> 00:29:36,000
[She's choking up from the compliments]

564
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:42,850
Being called the No. 1 in the industry
must've been a burden.

565
00:29:42,850 --> 00:29:47,510
But I think the good feedback is a relief to her.

566
00:29:48,240 --> 00:29:51,840
It's true. I've been referred to
as the No. 1 in the industry,

567
00:29:51,840 --> 00:29:53,700
but I'm a very timid person.

568
00:29:53,700 --> 00:30:00,950
I was worried my flaw as a director
would be revealed here.

569
00:30:01,630 --> 00:30:04,130
I was under a lot of pressure,

570
00:30:04,130 --> 00:30:07,560
but hearing your feedback...

571
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:09,500
I don't know.

572
00:30:11,070 --> 00:30:15,820
It felt like Director Lee was saying,
"You're on the right track."

573
00:30:15,820 --> 00:30:20,380
That was the feeling I got.

574
00:30:20,380 --> 00:30:22,970
That's why I got choked up.

575
00:30:23,700 --> 00:30:25,310
What did you think, Director Lee Hwan?

576
00:30:25,310 --> 00:30:27,850
I think I have...

577
00:30:30,900 --> 00:30:35,800
I think I have the opposite opinion.

578
00:30:37,610 --> 00:30:42,320
You made it fast-paced in a short-form style

579
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:44,310
like a technician.

580
00:30:44,310 --> 00:30:49,710
It felt like all the scenes were the same length.

581
00:30:49,710 --> 00:30:52,970
It felt fast-paced but boring.

582
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:57,600
It felt like I did watch something,
but something was skipped.

583
00:30:57,600 --> 00:31:01,500
I felt like I wasn't really sure what I watched.

584
00:31:01,500 --> 00:31:04,310
[Got both positive and negative feedback]

585
00:31:05,820 --> 00:31:07,780
[Final result announcement]

586
00:31:07,780 --> 00:31:11,770
Directors Yang Gyeong Hee and
Park So Rang's death match.

587
00:31:11,770 --> 00:31:17,980
We are awaiting the final result
that includes the Five Stars' votes.

588
00:31:17,980 --> 00:31:20,750
A visual master, Yang Gyeong Hee.

589
00:31:20,750 --> 00:31:23,670
Short drama hit maker, Park So Rang.

590
00:31:23,670 --> 00:31:28,140
What will be the result?

591
00:31:28,140 --> 00:31:33,900
Director Yang Gyeong Hee got
27 stops from the viewers.

592
00:31:33,900 --> 00:31:36,570
[More than 50% pressed the stop button]

593
00:31:36,570 --> 00:31:42,320
Director Park So Rang got
13 stops from the viewers.

594
00:31:43,110 --> 00:31:47,610
It looks like she's ahead with fewer stops,

595
00:31:47,610 --> 00:31:49,760
but it's too soon to relax.

596
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:53,140
The result could change based
on the Five Stars' votes.

597
00:31:53,140 --> 00:31:56,270
Who will win this battle?

598
00:31:56,300 --> 00:32:03,700
Here is the final result,
including the Five Stars' votes.

599
00:32:03,760 --> 00:32:06,150
[Park So Rang vs. Yang Gyeong Hee]

600
00:32:09,790 --> 00:32:11,800
I just thought I lost because

601
00:32:11,800 --> 00:32:17,550
I thought the viewers' opinions
would be similar to the judges'.

602
00:32:18,900 --> 00:32:21,300
I was so nervous.

603
00:32:21,300 --> 00:32:23,630
I thought I was going crazy.

604
00:32:23,630 --> 00:32:25,600
[13 stops vs. 27 stops]

605
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:26,830
Please reveal...

606
00:32:26,830 --> 00:32:29,280
[Can the 14-vote deficit be overturned?]

607
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,860
the final result.

608
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:36,200
[Shocked]

609
00:32:36,200 --> 00:32:38,300
[What's going on?]

610
00:32:41,860 --> 00:32:46,250
[Director Yang Gyeong Hee wins!]

611
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:50,720
[She overturned a 14-vote deficit]

612
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:54,350
[A twist from the Five Stars' votes]

613
00:32:54,350 --> 00:32:56,170
Wow, it was overturned.

614
00:32:56,170 --> 00:32:57,780
This is crazy.

615
00:32:57,780 --> 00:32:59,380
Three people voted, right?

616
00:32:59,380 --> 00:33:00,560
Two, two.

617
00:33:00,560 --> 00:33:04,090
Zero votes versus two votes.

618
00:33:04,090 --> 00:33:06,630
[Their fates swapped]

619
00:33:06,630 --> 00:33:09,270
Two judges voted. I think I know one of them.

620
00:33:09,270 --> 00:33:11,630
[Unintentionally revealed his vote]

621
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:15,550
He doesn't know how we do it because he's new.

622
00:33:15,550 --> 00:33:18,550
[Their secrets always get revealed]

623
00:33:18,550 --> 00:33:21,480
It's important to be critical.

624
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:23,690
So, this can happen.

625
00:33:23,690 --> 00:33:26,600
You won the battle, Director Yang.
How do you feel?

626
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:30,090
The votes suddenly got flipped.

627
00:33:30,090 --> 00:33:32,210
I feel a little bad.

628
00:33:33,160 --> 00:33:36,330
I know how hard she worked.

629
00:33:37,120 --> 00:33:41,290
I'm not so sure. But thank you.

630
00:33:41,290 --> 00:33:45,480
Directors Yang Gyeong Hee
and Park So Rang, thank you.

631
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:47,000
Thank you.

632
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:49,340
[Their passion outshone the result]

633
00:33:49,970 --> 00:33:52,870
I've never won the lottery.

634
00:33:52,870 --> 00:33:56,110
I feel like the universe is helping me.

635
00:33:56,110 --> 00:34:00,710
I thought I was falling into the fire pit,

636
00:34:00,710 --> 00:34:04,210
but I was fished out of it.

637
00:34:04,210 --> 00:34:06,710
It was a relief.

638
00:34:06,710 --> 00:34:10,250
The unavoidable cutthroat
battle, a 1:1 death match.

639
00:34:10,250 --> 00:34:13,480
Let's welcome the next two directors.

640
00:34:13,480 --> 00:34:15,180
[Who will it be?]

641
00:34:15,180 --> 00:34:16,980
[Nervous]

642
00:34:16,980 --> 00:34:21,560
Yesterday's friends became enemies.

643
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:22,890
It's these two.

644
00:34:22,890 --> 00:34:25,640
He gained attention with
high-quality cinematography.

645
00:34:25,640 --> 00:34:28,770
Master of quality control, Director Jeong Joo.

646
00:34:28,770 --> 00:34:31,400
He has an untouchable, unique style.

647
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:33,720
A master of absurd B-movies.

648
00:34:33,720 --> 00:34:36,970
Director Han Sang Il. Please come forward.

649
00:34:36,970 --> 00:34:40,750
[Leaving with a fighting spirit!]

650
00:34:41,730 --> 00:34:43,980
[Revealing their thumbnails first]

651
00:34:43,980 --> 00:34:46,130
Oh, this one.

652
00:34:46,130 --> 00:34:48,920
Wow, they're totally different.

653
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:52,480
This is powerful. They're total opposites.

654
00:34:53,160 --> 00:34:54,530
Did the poster change?

655
00:34:54,530 --> 00:34:57,450
Only the one for "No Humans" changed.

656
00:34:57,450 --> 00:35:00,360
[Changed the thumbnail for Round 3]

657
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:02,450
[Director Han Sang Il kept the same thumbnail]

658
00:35:02,450 --> 00:35:06,110
Looks like Director Han's didn't change.

659
00:35:06,110 --> 00:35:07,960
Does it mean he's confident?

660
00:35:07,960 --> 00:35:10,330
[Prepared Jeong Joo vs. confident Han Sang Il]

661
00:35:10,330 --> 00:35:12,930
- Here they come.
- Welcome.

662
00:35:12,930 --> 00:35:17,380
Yesterday's friends became today's enemies.

663
00:35:17,380 --> 00:35:21,430
They had amazing chemistry in Round 2.

664
00:35:21,430 --> 00:35:23,370
- Absurd humor.
- Visual.

665
00:35:23,370 --> 00:35:25,360
- We're the best.
- We're the best.

666
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:28,790
It's so hard to watch.

667
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:32,230
[Han Sang Il's "My Love Story
Only I Don't Know About"]

668
00:35:32,230 --> 00:35:35,110
- It's short and powerful.
- It was amazing.

669
00:35:35,110 --> 00:35:39,240
Director Han Sang Il survived. Congratulations.

670
00:35:39,240 --> 00:35:42,550
[Director Jeong Joo's "No Humans"]

671
00:35:43,140 --> 00:35:47,160
[The high-quality visuals shocked everyone]

672
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:49,980
[A B-movie vs. A-grade polished cinematography]

673
00:35:50,620 --> 00:35:54,510
[And the partnership of these two
very different people turned out to be?]

674
00:35:54,510 --> 00:35:55,760
[Average viewing time: 107.36 seconds]

675
00:35:55,760 --> 00:35:58,770
[Second place in Round 2! A fantastic duo!]

676
00:35:58,770 --> 00:36:01,070
I have nothing to criticize. I loved it.

677
00:36:01,070 --> 00:36:03,190
It makes you want to watch it again.

678
00:36:03,190 --> 00:36:04,900
I even thought I'd like to work with you.

679
00:36:04,900 --> 00:36:06,860
Thank you.

680
00:36:06,860 --> 00:36:09,480
[But!]

681
00:36:09,780 --> 00:36:12,820
I'll make you a variety show star.

682
00:36:12,820 --> 00:36:14,100
Director Jeong Joo, come out.

683
00:36:14,100 --> 00:36:15,940
[Unexpected betrayal]

684
00:36:15,940 --> 00:36:18,620
[Explosive dopamine]

685
00:36:18,620 --> 00:36:20,080
[It's always fun to observe other people's drama]

686
00:36:20,080 --> 00:36:22,520
This is fun. This is fun.

687
00:36:22,520 --> 00:36:25,150
[The battle has begun]

688
00:36:25,150 --> 00:36:27,450
How do you honestly feel right now?

689
00:36:27,450 --> 00:36:30,710
I understand his style completely.

690
00:36:30,710 --> 00:36:32,770
I studied it thoroughly.

691
00:36:32,770 --> 00:36:35,360
I think I can easily win.

692
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:37,270
It's not something you can just copy.

693
00:36:37,270 --> 00:36:39,430
[Bloody mind game even before the battle begins]

694
00:36:39,430 --> 00:36:41,670
Wow. Go, go, go!

695
00:36:41,670 --> 00:36:44,020
It was easy to copy him.

696
00:36:44,020 --> 00:36:45,510
This is fun.

697
00:36:45,510 --> 00:36:48,260
[Fun to watch]

698
00:36:48,750 --> 00:36:51,960
He visited my set.

699
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:54,080
[Han Sang Il visited Jeong Joo's set?]

700
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:56,090
He was shooting near my neighborhood.

701
00:36:56,090 --> 00:36:57,320
It's true.

702
00:36:57,320 --> 00:37:00,260
So, I visited him to bother him.

703
00:37:00,260 --> 00:37:01,860
You didn't set up push pins, did you?

704
00:37:01,860 --> 00:37:05,430
He came to the set and created commotion.

705
00:37:06,190 --> 00:37:09,560
[A set with an unusual vibe]

706
00:37:09,990 --> 00:37:13,500
[Zombies come alive early in the morning]

707
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:16,920
You will be doing challenging acting today.

708
00:37:16,920 --> 00:37:20,500
[Custom-made fake blood]

709
00:37:20,500 --> 00:37:23,640
[Jeong Joo is fine-tuning the set and makeup]

710
00:37:24,330 --> 00:37:29,620
You need something provocative in a short drama.

711
00:37:29,620 --> 00:37:32,170
So, I focused on that a lot.

712
00:37:32,170 --> 00:37:33,630
Action.

713
00:37:33,630 --> 00:37:37,160
[The villagers escaped to the
rooftop to escape the zombies]

714
00:37:38,060 --> 00:37:39,740
Again, again. Cut, cut.

715
00:37:39,740 --> 00:37:43,000
[Switching scenes quickly for a dopamine rush]

716
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,220
[The camera movement to keep you on edge]

717
00:37:45,220 --> 00:37:49,430
[Keep the angles extreme!]

718
00:37:49,790 --> 00:37:53,190
- Cut. Okay, I love it.
- Okay!

719
00:37:53,190 --> 00:37:56,610
Director Han Sang Il lives in the neighborhood.

720
00:37:56,610 --> 00:37:58,560
He picked these up for us.

721
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:00,230
Thank you.

722
00:38:00,230 --> 00:38:02,350
Your team needs to fail.

723
00:38:03,270 --> 00:38:05,840
[Lurking]

724
00:38:05,840 --> 00:38:07,780
Do you have any extra storyboard handouts?

725
00:38:07,780 --> 00:38:10,010
- Any extra storyboard handouts?
- Storyboard handout?

726
00:38:10,010 --> 00:38:12,910
[Sharing the storyboard without hesitation]

727
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:16,800
No one can beat me even if I share my secrets.

728
00:38:18,040 --> 00:38:20,040
This is too...

729
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:23,200
- It's too descriptive.
- I changed it.

730
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:24,560
- You did?
- Yes.

731
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:26,580
Give me the new storyboard, then.

732
00:38:27,230 --> 00:38:29,000
I change things on set.

733
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:31,110
He hated it when I did that last time.

734
00:38:31,110 --> 00:38:33,570
I learned it from you.
I learned how to freestyle.

735
00:38:33,570 --> 00:38:36,620
I'm totally absorbed in this show.

736
00:38:36,620 --> 00:38:41,740
I gave up on the style I was going for.

737
00:38:41,740 --> 00:38:44,270
I'm trying to make it comical.

738
00:38:44,910 --> 00:38:47,140
[He's visiting this place for his victory]

739
00:38:47,140 --> 00:38:52,740
AI creates realistic visuals
that are hard to shoot.

740
00:38:52,740 --> 00:38:54,610
[Which AI scene did he hire them for?]

741
00:38:54,610 --> 00:38:56,700
Oh, my God.

742
00:38:56,700 --> 00:39:01,490
You need a shot showing
it's a redevelopment area.

743
00:39:01,490 --> 00:39:05,290
I wasn't allowed to shoot because
it's a redevelopment area.

744
00:39:05,290 --> 00:39:07,510
[A drone shot that looks more
realistic than actual footage]

745
00:39:07,510 --> 00:39:09,970
This will be good for introducing
the world in the beginning.

746
00:39:09,970 --> 00:39:12,300
And now the cockroach scene.

747
00:39:12,300 --> 00:39:14,080
[Hello]

748
00:39:14,080 --> 00:39:15,710
It said hello.

749
00:39:15,710 --> 00:39:17,380
I'm so happy with it.

750
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:21,500
The cockroach is too pretty
right now. It's shiny.

751
00:39:21,530 --> 00:39:23,620
[Falling in love with the AI cockroach]

752
00:39:23,620 --> 00:39:25,950
I'll film it and edit it well.

753
00:39:25,950 --> 00:39:28,770
I'll win this round and head
for the victory, too.

754
00:39:29,580 --> 00:39:33,770
And please introduce "No Humans."

755
00:39:33,770 --> 00:39:37,490
It's a zombie scam story that
unfolds in a redevelopment area.

756
00:39:37,490 --> 00:39:40,020
Korean people like loud actions.

757
00:39:40,020 --> 00:39:44,920
I hope you enjoy the loud actions
from the villagers.

758
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:47,670
- I'm excited about this one.
- "No Humans"?

759
00:39:47,670 --> 00:39:50,030
Director Jeong Joo is good.

760
00:39:50,030 --> 00:39:51,710
I'm excited.

761
00:39:51,710 --> 00:39:53,800
[Only one person wants him to fail]

762
00:39:54,460 --> 00:39:57,320
I'm confident in the cinematic aspects.

763
00:39:57,320 --> 00:40:02,820
I used some of his B-movie
qualities this time, too.

764
00:40:02,820 --> 00:40:04,910
So, I think I could easily win.

765
00:40:04,910 --> 00:40:07,460
["No Humans"]

766
00:40:07,860 --> 00:40:12,840
[Jeong Joo's "No Humans" Episode 1]

767
00:40:13,700 --> 00:40:14,960
[Do Yun]

768
00:40:17,210 --> 00:40:18,970
[Yun Jeong]

769
00:40:26,810 --> 00:40:27,730
Don't come near me.

770
00:40:27,730 --> 00:40:29,640
I'll kill you if you do.

771
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:30,680
What? What?

772
00:40:30,700 --> 00:40:32,670
- I'll kill you.
- No! You'll get hurt!

773
00:40:32,670 --> 00:40:35,020
What are you doing, Honey?

774
00:40:39,580 --> 00:40:40,530
Seriously.

775
00:40:40,530 --> 00:40:42,010
[Hehe]

776
00:40:42,010 --> 00:40:45,130
[Jeong Joo's comedy is getting reactions!]

777
00:40:45,130 --> 00:40:47,290
[Nervous]

778
00:40:47,980 --> 00:40:50,250
[Is the stop count really zero?]

779
00:40:53,060 --> 00:40:54,760
Seriously.

780
00:40:57,640 --> 00:41:00,260
Get off my son! Hey!

781
00:41:06,220 --> 00:41:08,070
Good job.

782
00:41:09,310 --> 00:41:11,280
Sorry, sorry.

783
00:41:17,460 --> 00:41:18,900
No!

784
00:41:18,900 --> 00:41:20,510
Gosh, she got bitten.

785
00:41:20,510 --> 00:41:22,580
[They're getting sucked into the zombie show]

786
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:32,270
[No one has pressed a button yet]

787
00:41:32,770 --> 00:41:33,970
I'm in trouble.

788
00:41:33,970 --> 00:41:36,720
Fail, fail, fail...

789
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:41,130
We got a new zombie here.

790
00:41:41,130 --> 00:41:45,210
[The stop count is going up
as the second zombie shows up]

791
00:41:47,150 --> 00:41:50,000
As the second zombie showed up,

792
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:52,130
the stop count suddenly went up.

793
00:41:52,130 --> 00:41:54,220
I wondered if something was off.

794
00:41:54,220 --> 00:41:58,730
I added that because I thought it was fun.

795
00:41:58,730 --> 00:42:02,300
But people started pressing
the button at that point.

796
00:42:03,660 --> 00:42:05,410
Everyone, run to the rooftop. Hurry.

797
00:42:05,410 --> 00:42:07,190
Go, go, go!

798
00:42:08,250 --> 00:42:10,420
Mom, what are you doing?

799
00:42:10,420 --> 00:42:12,750
Shut the window and stay inside. Now.

800
00:42:14,530 --> 00:42:16,630
A bamboo spear?

801
00:42:20,290 --> 00:42:22,690
No, but how?

802
00:42:22,690 --> 00:42:25,220
911, what's your emergency?

803
00:42:25,220 --> 00:42:27,290
He's calling 911?

804
00:42:27,290 --> 00:42:29,200
What's going on?

805
00:42:29,200 --> 00:42:31,310
[Episode 2 starts]

806
00:42:31,310 --> 00:42:32,960
["No Humans" Episode 2]

807
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:35,580
- We got it.
- Go, go.

808
00:42:38,380 --> 00:42:40,290
Hurry, hurry.

809
00:42:44,540 --> 00:42:47,070
Ri Ah. We need to bring Ri Ah.

810
00:42:47,070 --> 00:42:49,460
How can you say that right now?

811
00:42:49,460 --> 00:42:52,950
[The stop count is already over 20]

812
00:42:52,950 --> 00:42:56,070
The voting is cutthroat today.

813
00:42:56,070 --> 00:42:58,920
[Zoning out...]

814
00:42:58,920 --> 00:43:01,790
The numbers started going up halfway through.

815
00:43:01,790 --> 00:43:03,940
I thought I had a shot.

816
00:43:06,510 --> 00:43:09,990
The lady from No. 202 got bitten.

817
00:43:09,990 --> 00:43:13,130
What if her eyes get flipped over?

818
00:43:13,130 --> 00:43:14,340
No.

819
00:43:14,340 --> 00:43:15,450
I'm totally fine.

820
00:43:15,450 --> 00:43:18,730
No, you are not. I saw the
zombie biting you earlier.

821
00:43:18,730 --> 00:43:21,020
No, look at me.

822
00:43:22,870 --> 00:43:26,740
If you compare this to the Rage Virus
in the movie "28 Days Later,"

823
00:43:26,740 --> 00:43:31,240
she'll turn into a zombie 99.9% of the
time within 60 seconds of exposure.

824
00:43:31,300 --> 00:43:32,660
We have five seconds left.

825
00:43:32,660 --> 00:43:34,000
Five.

826
00:43:34,060 --> 00:43:35,490
Four.

827
00:43:35,490 --> 00:43:37,090
Three.

828
00:43:37,090 --> 00:43:38,620
Two.

829
00:43:41,900 --> 00:43:43,760
One!

830
00:43:44,750 --> 00:43:46,350
No!

831
00:43:48,750 --> 00:43:53,040
[The last dopamine rush stopped
people from pushing the button]

832
00:44:02,530 --> 00:44:04,060
How could you just kill her?

833
00:44:04,060 --> 00:44:06,560
We don't know if she's a human,
an animal, or a monster.

834
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:08,260
You didn't kill a human.

835
00:44:08,260 --> 00:44:11,700
Honey, you saved the whole family.

836
00:44:17,730 --> 00:44:20,550
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

837
00:44:20,550 --> 00:44:24,270
Director Jeong Joo's video ended.

838
00:44:24,270 --> 00:44:29,230
You received 27 stops in total.

839
00:44:30,110 --> 00:44:33,720
I didn't think I would get so many.

840
00:44:33,720 --> 00:44:39,210
I didn't think the result would
be so devastating.

841
00:44:39,210 --> 00:44:40,980
I was shocked.

842
00:44:40,980 --> 00:44:46,110
I don't think the first person was
a zombie because he called 911.

843
00:44:46,110 --> 00:44:47,680
Looks like he was just injured.

844
00:44:47,680 --> 00:44:49,800
The secret regarding that gets revealed later.

845
00:44:49,800 --> 00:44:53,060
The story structure is nothing
like other zombie flicks.

846
00:44:53,060 --> 00:44:57,370
It could be the organization's plot
to remove the residents.

847
00:44:57,370 --> 00:45:01,600
Yes, it's also a social commentary.

848
00:45:01,600 --> 00:45:04,690
I love stuff like this. It's fun to watch,

849
00:45:04,690 --> 00:45:09,400
but you give us something to
think about. I think that's great.

850
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:11,580
It could leave an impact.

851
00:45:11,580 --> 00:45:15,420
I'm curious what Director Eun Jong Hun thought.

852
00:45:15,420 --> 00:45:17,150
I enjoyed it.

853
00:45:17,150 --> 00:45:20,220
But I... well...

854
00:45:20,220 --> 00:45:21,530
pressed the stop button.

855
00:45:21,530 --> 00:45:23,460
[Why would you say that?]

856
00:45:23,460 --> 00:45:25,650
[It hurts]

857
00:45:25,650 --> 00:45:27,740
You're eliminated. Another director, please.

858
00:45:27,740 --> 00:45:28,930
I'm sorry.

859
00:45:28,930 --> 00:45:31,410
Why, why? What made you?

860
00:45:32,140 --> 00:45:36,300
I think I pressed it when many other viewers did.

861
00:45:36,300 --> 00:45:38,700
[The stop count skyrocketed
when the second zombie showed up]

862
00:45:39,750 --> 00:45:42,090
[Adding a vote]

863
00:45:42,860 --> 00:45:47,540
I understood they were fighting the zombies.

864
00:45:47,540 --> 00:45:49,370
But I couldn't feel anything.

865
00:45:49,370 --> 00:45:50,930
Things were moving quickly, but I was confused.

866
00:45:50,930 --> 00:45:55,160
That left me feeling a bit disappointed.

867
00:45:55,160 --> 00:45:58,210
The zombie genre in general

868
00:45:58,210 --> 00:46:04,250
is hard to pull off with a short drama budget.

869
00:46:04,250 --> 00:46:06,250
To overcome that,

870
00:46:06,250 --> 00:46:10,420
I think you need a sensational and unique idea.

871
00:46:10,420 --> 00:46:13,510
It seemed like you had it, but I didn't see it.

872
00:46:15,430 --> 00:46:18,680
I think Director Han's sabotage worked.

873
00:46:22,050 --> 00:46:25,260
The comedy didn't work.

874
00:46:25,260 --> 00:46:27,290
It was disappointing. It was chaotic.

875
00:46:27,290 --> 00:46:30,340
You said you added a social commentary,

876
00:46:30,340 --> 00:46:33,420
but you see that a lot in zombie flicks.

877
00:46:33,420 --> 00:46:35,680
It was nothing new.

878
00:46:38,190 --> 00:46:42,750
The judges have been praising me a lot,

879
00:46:42,750 --> 00:46:45,320
but they were harsh to me today.

880
00:46:45,320 --> 00:46:47,330
I'm a bit upset.

881
00:46:47,330 --> 00:46:50,530
[The critique for Director Jeong Joo ended]

882
00:46:51,190 --> 00:46:53,430
[Director Han Sang Il is
coming up, feeling pressured]

883
00:46:53,840 --> 00:46:55,310
Okay.

884
00:46:55,310 --> 00:46:58,580
Let me ask you directly.

885
00:46:58,580 --> 00:47:00,460
What did you think of
Director Jeong Joo's short drama?

886
00:47:00,460 --> 00:47:02,850
[Everyone wants to know what he thinks]

887
00:47:02,850 --> 00:47:05,090
Should I be nice or not?

888
00:47:05,090 --> 00:47:08,950
I guess I want to ask if you think you could win.

889
00:47:08,950 --> 00:47:10,270
[Need popcorn for this]

890
00:47:10,270 --> 00:47:14,620
To be positive, his style is
totally different than mine.

891
00:47:15,400 --> 00:47:18,860
To be negative, I said you can't copy me.

892
00:47:19,550 --> 00:47:20,780
[Intense]

893
00:47:20,780 --> 00:47:24,030
What made him turn into a thug?

894
00:47:24,940 --> 00:47:27,620
He was meant to be on TV.

895
00:47:27,620 --> 00:47:30,420
There is a way to make people laugh.

896
00:47:30,420 --> 00:47:35,850
But I think he was a bit
heavy-handed regarding that.

897
00:47:35,850 --> 00:47:39,070
Comedy is definitely your specialty.

898
00:47:39,070 --> 00:47:44,580
I saw the cast.
Wanna One's Park Woo Jin is in it.

899
00:47:44,580 --> 00:47:49,000
[The main dancer who dominates the stage]

900
00:47:49,000 --> 00:47:51,180
[He's giving short drama a try]

901
00:47:51,180 --> 00:47:56,150
Did he adjust okay to your comedic sensibility?

902
00:47:56,150 --> 00:47:57,720
He struggled a bit.

903
00:47:57,720 --> 00:48:00,470
There's a certain scene.

904
00:48:00,470 --> 00:48:03,200
["My Love Story Only I Don't Know About" set]

905
00:48:03,530 --> 00:48:05,120
[Massage gun]

906
00:48:05,120 --> 00:48:07,290
[His work and life are a B-movie]

907
00:48:07,290 --> 00:48:10,880
Director, when I'm shocked
to hear about my boyfriend,

908
00:48:10,880 --> 00:48:13,180
- should I be like, "What?"
- You only think that.

909
00:48:13,180 --> 00:48:14,580
Only think that?

910
00:48:14,580 --> 00:48:16,680
[Ye Rin doesn't remember her
boyfriend after getting hit by a dog house]

911
00:48:16,680 --> 00:48:19,330
[Who's playing Ye Rin's boyfriend, Gi Tak?]

912
00:48:19,330 --> 00:48:20,900
[Here he is]

913
00:48:20,900 --> 00:48:23,070
[Park Woo Jin is playing Gi Tak, the boyfriend]

914
00:48:24,200 --> 00:48:28,060
[Can he work with
Director Han's directing style?]

915
00:48:29,200 --> 00:48:31,840
[The scene where Ye Rin is shocked to see Gi Tak]

916
00:48:31,840 --> 00:48:34,400
You have to laugh unnaturally.
It has to be bizarre.

917
00:48:34,400 --> 00:48:36,490
[Park Woo Jin is trying
to act as weirdly as possible]

918
00:48:36,490 --> 00:48:38,350
Try to make it more unnatural.

919
00:48:38,350 --> 00:48:40,160
This is probably scarier.

920
00:48:40,160 --> 00:48:42,000
Place your arms like this.

921
00:48:42,000 --> 00:48:43,750
Stop looking at me.

922
00:48:43,750 --> 00:48:45,500
You're trying to be like...

923
00:48:45,500 --> 00:48:48,090
- You creep me out.
- Do that on purpose.

924
00:48:48,090 --> 00:48:50,310
- You creep me out.
- Like this?

925
00:48:50,310 --> 00:48:52,330
[He can follow orders]

926
00:48:52,330 --> 00:48:53,890
That's it.

927
00:48:53,890 --> 00:48:58,070
The strange movements reveal
more about the character.

928
00:48:58,070 --> 00:48:59,620
Is this a thriller?

929
00:48:59,620 --> 00:49:01,080
Yes, it's a thriller.

930
00:49:01,080 --> 00:49:03,300
In this scene, yes.

931
00:49:04,360 --> 00:49:06,970
[It must have been hard to
understand his directions]

932
00:49:06,970 --> 00:49:09,950
It's more like I was flustered.

933
00:49:09,950 --> 00:49:12,990
I wasn't sure if it was right.

934
00:49:12,990 --> 00:49:14,650
But I don't have a lot of experience.

935
00:49:14,650 --> 00:49:18,150
So, I trusted him because he knows a lot more.

936
00:49:18,920 --> 00:49:21,760
[Understood the absurd tone after monitoring]

937
00:49:22,790 --> 00:49:25,420
It's my incredible directing ability.

938
00:49:27,420 --> 00:49:29,990
I didn't know we were only showing two episodes.

939
00:49:29,990 --> 00:49:34,270
So, I added the twist in Episode 3.

940
00:49:34,270 --> 00:49:36,650
[Happy to hear it]

941
00:49:37,920 --> 00:49:40,110
I was told we are only playing two episodes.

942
00:49:40,110 --> 00:49:43,290
The highlight is in Episode 3.

943
00:49:43,290 --> 00:49:46,810
I first heard it when I arrived
at the studio today.

944
00:49:46,810 --> 00:49:48,410
He's lying.

945
00:49:49,410 --> 00:49:50,990
He is trying to convince the judges.

946
00:49:50,990 --> 00:49:53,800
Boo. No more. Boo.

947
00:49:53,800 --> 00:49:55,980
It makes no sense.

948
00:49:56,750 --> 00:50:00,440
The first two episodes are an intro.

949
00:50:00,440 --> 00:50:03,720
And we don't get to see the highlight today.

950
00:50:03,720 --> 00:50:05,790
[Hehe]

951
00:50:05,790 --> 00:50:07,480
[Off to a rocky start]

952
00:50:07,480 --> 00:50:11,060
Actually, my teaser was Episode 1.

953
00:50:11,060 --> 00:50:13,430
So, I repeated Episode 1.

954
00:50:13,430 --> 00:50:17,190
I don't know if they'll react
negatively or be understanding.

955
00:50:17,190 --> 00:50:19,960
I'm a bit worried about that.

956
00:50:21,300 --> 00:50:25,920
Now we'll start the video.

957
00:50:25,920 --> 00:50:30,090
"My Love Story Only I Don't Know About."
Play the video.

958
00:50:30,090 --> 00:50:33,600
["My Love Story Only I Don't Know About"]

959
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:37,630
Totally unexpected events happen sometimes.

960
00:50:37,630 --> 00:50:40,000
Lady, dodge!

961
00:50:44,310 --> 00:50:46,270
[It's still shocking]

962
00:50:46,270 --> 00:50:48,140
[We already saw this]

963
00:50:48,790 --> 00:50:51,680
When I woke up...

964
00:50:51,680 --> 00:50:53,430
I think we've seen this.

965
00:50:53,430 --> 00:50:55,590
He's replaying the teaser.

966
00:50:56,310 --> 00:50:58,310
It's what he made last time.

967
00:50:58,310 --> 00:51:00,840
I just need to overcome Episode 1.

968
00:51:02,400 --> 00:51:04,470
I got hit by a flying doghouse.

969
00:51:04,470 --> 00:51:06,650
I was in a coma for three months.

970
00:51:06,650 --> 00:51:08,850
When I woke up,

971
00:51:08,850 --> 00:51:11,700
I saw the doctor who recently got divorced.

972
00:51:11,700 --> 00:51:12,620
And...

973
00:51:12,620 --> 00:51:14,760
Ye Rin, are you awake?

974
00:51:14,760 --> 00:51:16,330
Who are you?

975
00:51:16,330 --> 00:51:18,000
What's wrong with her?

976
00:51:18,000 --> 00:51:20,410
Wake up, Ye Rin. It's Mom.

977
00:51:20,410 --> 00:51:22,610
She might have temporarily lost
her memory from the shock.

978
00:51:22,610 --> 00:51:24,420
I'll crack her brain open.

979
00:51:24,420 --> 00:51:26,440
I was joking, Mom.

980
00:51:27,290 --> 00:51:28,710
How could I forget you, Mom?

981
00:51:28,710 --> 00:51:31,560
You scared me, you brat.

982
00:51:35,680 --> 00:51:37,660
By the way,

983
00:51:37,660 --> 00:51:39,320
It's Park Woo Jin.

984
00:51:40,730 --> 00:51:42,040
By the way,

985
00:51:42,040 --> 00:51:45,660
who's trying to molest me in broad daylight?

986
00:51:46,830 --> 00:51:48,710
You're gutsier than you look.

987
00:51:48,710 --> 00:51:51,030
With so many eyewitnesses.

988
00:51:51,030 --> 00:51:53,540
I won't settle, just so you know.

989
00:51:53,540 --> 00:51:55,890
Gosh, what's with you?

990
00:51:56,750 --> 00:51:59,780
He's your boyfriend, Gi Tak.

991
00:52:03,770 --> 00:52:05,210
This happens from time to time.

992
00:52:05,210 --> 00:52:09,100
People lose only certain memories.

993
00:52:09,100 --> 00:52:10,550
That can't be.

994
00:52:10,550 --> 00:52:12,700
I know it's confusing, but you need to accept it.

995
00:52:12,700 --> 00:52:15,320
I care about the looks more than you think.

996
00:52:15,320 --> 00:52:19,870
I don't know why anyone would date someone

997
00:52:19,870 --> 00:52:21,970
with such a topsy-turvy face.

998
00:52:21,970 --> 00:52:24,040
Here's another nutcase.

999
00:52:27,130 --> 00:52:28,280
Huh?

1000
00:52:28,280 --> 00:52:30,730
That's where it ends.

1001
00:52:30,730 --> 00:52:33,130
Was that a good place to end?

1002
00:52:34,270 --> 00:52:39,210
[Will the ending timing get people to stop?]

1003
00:52:40,690 --> 00:52:42,360
The count kept going up.

1004
00:52:42,360 --> 00:52:44,680
I was like, "Why is my video so long?"

1005
00:52:44,680 --> 00:52:45,920
["My Love Story Only
I Don't Know About" Episode 2]

1006
00:52:45,920 --> 00:52:48,840
I must have dated him
because he loved me so much.

1007
00:52:48,840 --> 00:52:51,860
Huh? What are you talking about?

1008
00:52:51,860 --> 00:52:55,890
You were the one who
begged him to go out with you.

1009
00:52:57,800 --> 00:53:01,420
- Look.
- Gi Tak says he doesn't like me.

1010
00:53:02,070 --> 00:53:05,980
I'm going to die. Give me rat poison.
Strawberry flavor.

1011
00:53:05,980 --> 00:53:08,860
I liked him that much?

1012
00:53:09,990 --> 00:53:11,160
Ye Rin.

1013
00:53:11,910 --> 00:53:14,580
Move.

1014
00:53:14,580 --> 00:53:16,270
[LOL]

1015
00:53:16,270 --> 00:53:17,770
[Random comedic moment]

1016
00:53:17,770 --> 00:53:19,070
Why did he slap him?

1017
00:53:19,730 --> 00:53:21,770
This is funny. This is funny.

1018
00:53:21,770 --> 00:53:23,290
[I don't find it funny]

1019
00:53:28,350 --> 00:53:29,550
Ye Rin.

1020
00:53:30,540 --> 00:53:31,910
Move.

1021
00:53:33,250 --> 00:53:34,890
I was so worried about you.

1022
00:53:34,890 --> 00:53:36,020
Your eyes are finally open...

1023
00:53:36,020 --> 00:53:38,230
W-What's with your mug?

1024
00:53:38,230 --> 00:53:39,830
- E-Excuse me.
- Ye Rin.

1025
00:53:39,830 --> 00:53:43,150
I would've flirted with him
if I were 30 years younger.

1026
00:53:43,150 --> 00:53:45,630
Who's this handsome man?

1027
00:53:46,730 --> 00:53:47,730
Hello, ma'am.

1028
00:53:47,730 --> 00:53:51,970
I'm Ye Rin's secret lover, Kang Hyeon Su.

1029
00:53:51,970 --> 00:53:55,160
To put it simply, I'm the other man.

1030
00:53:55,160 --> 00:53:57,170
You're slutty just like me.

1031
00:53:57,170 --> 00:54:00,160
I told you not to get caught.

1032
00:54:00,160 --> 00:54:01,630
Excuse me.

1033
00:54:01,630 --> 00:54:04,000
What is it? Tell me.

1034
00:54:04,000 --> 00:54:07,360
Team Leader Hyeon Su, stop goofing around.

1035
00:54:08,850 --> 00:54:12,290
What did you hear? Do you want to get sued?

1036
00:54:12,290 --> 00:54:14,750
I heard you no longer recognize your boyfriend.

1037
00:54:14,750 --> 00:54:18,390
How could you play tricks using my condition?

1038
00:54:18,390 --> 00:54:21,000
What a shitty person you are.

1039
00:54:21,000 --> 00:54:22,590
Don't be so harsh on me.

1040
00:54:22,590 --> 00:54:25,680
I gave it a try because
I thought it was my chance.

1041
00:54:25,680 --> 00:54:26,980
Pardon?

1042
00:54:26,980 --> 00:54:30,290
You remember what I said two years ago, right?

1043
00:54:34,770 --> 00:54:36,900
[Episode 2 finished playing]

1044
00:54:36,900 --> 00:54:40,130
Director Han Sang Il's video ended.

1045
00:54:40,130 --> 00:54:45,770
You received 18 stops from the viewers.

1046
00:54:46,870 --> 00:54:49,130
I missed it when it happened.

1047
00:54:49,130 --> 00:54:52,970
Did Director Lee Beom Gyu
make a cameo appearance?

1048
00:54:52,970 --> 00:54:56,470
Yes, Beom Gyu helped me a lot.

1049
00:54:56,470 --> 00:54:57,620
Was he a patient? Who was he?

1050
00:54:57,620 --> 00:54:59,120
I got slapped.

1051
00:54:59,120 --> 00:55:01,530
- That was you?
- Right, right.

1052
00:55:02,660 --> 00:55:03,950
Yes, it was me.

1053
00:55:03,950 --> 00:55:06,160
[When the team leader first appeared]

1054
00:55:06,160 --> 00:55:09,120
[Director Lee Beom Gyu]

1055
00:55:09,120 --> 00:55:14,050
Director Han asked me to be a producer.

1056
00:55:14,050 --> 00:55:16,610
So, I helped him as a producer.

1057
00:55:16,610 --> 00:55:18,380
You're a producer now?

1058
00:55:18,380 --> 00:55:21,100
You've been so busy.

1059
00:55:21,100 --> 00:55:23,860
That's why he doesn't get to vote today.

1060
00:55:23,860 --> 00:55:25,720
He doesn't because we have to be fair.

1061
00:55:25,720 --> 00:55:27,000
That's true.

1062
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:30,140
So, I'm just enjoying the shows. It's fun.

1063
00:55:30,140 --> 00:55:32,240
[What will the judges say about it?]

1064
00:55:32,240 --> 00:55:34,910
Let's hear what the Five Stars thought.

1065
00:55:34,910 --> 00:55:36,600
[Nervous]

1066
00:55:36,600 --> 00:55:41,360
I'm curious about
Director Lee Byeong Heon's directing style.

1067
00:55:41,360 --> 00:55:46,680
Do you purposely produce B-movies or
use absurd humor in your movies?

1068
00:55:46,680 --> 00:55:48,220
What's the difference?

1069
00:55:48,220 --> 00:55:50,270
I do my best to make A-level movies,

1070
00:55:50,270 --> 00:55:51,990
but people keep calling them B-movies.

1071
00:55:51,990 --> 00:55:54,210
You just get labeled that way. What a shame.

1072
00:55:54,210 --> 00:55:56,810
- I'm the same.
- That was my impression, too.

1073
00:55:56,810 --> 00:55:58,560
That's sad, then.

1074
00:55:58,560 --> 00:56:02,800
The level of absurdity was like Director Lee's.

1075
00:56:02,800 --> 00:56:04,990
You know the slapping scene?

1076
00:56:04,990 --> 00:56:08,840
I thought that was a bit off the track.

1077
00:56:08,840 --> 00:56:10,650
My opinion is different.

1078
00:56:10,650 --> 00:56:13,790
- I know it's different.
- I wanted it to go all out.

1079
00:56:13,790 --> 00:56:16,940
I think he should have slapped
him and flipped him over.

1080
00:56:16,940 --> 00:56:18,120
I take it further.

1081
00:56:18,120 --> 00:56:21,880
I found the mother character so funny.

1082
00:56:21,880 --> 00:56:26,040
I liked how he stroked the mother's hand.

1083
00:56:26,040 --> 00:56:27,900
That was funny. Stuff like that is funny.

1084
00:56:27,900 --> 00:56:32,070
You could think it's off the rails
based on your taste.

1085
00:56:32,070 --> 00:56:35,340
Sometimes it's funny, sometimes it's too much.

1086
00:56:35,340 --> 00:56:37,580
[Two judges were in disagreement
due to a taste difference]

1087
00:56:37,600 --> 00:56:40,470
What did the two directors think?

1088
00:56:40,470 --> 00:56:44,770
[They gave a lot of harsh criticisms today]

1089
00:56:44,770 --> 00:56:46,410
[Heart racing]

1090
00:56:46,410 --> 00:56:48,740
First of all...

1091
00:56:48,740 --> 00:56:51,320
[Focused]

1092
00:56:51,320 --> 00:56:54,640
First of all, I enjoyed it.

1093
00:56:54,640 --> 00:56:56,420
[Gulp]

1094
00:56:56,420 --> 00:56:59,230
I thought the characters were animated.

1095
00:56:59,230 --> 00:57:02,890
I got drawn in because of the characters.

1096
00:57:02,890 --> 00:57:07,530
I think that helped me stay focused.

1097
00:57:09,910 --> 00:57:13,460
Why did I find this so boring?

1098
00:57:13,460 --> 00:57:17,870
Why is that? Why does it feel so repetitive?

1099
00:57:17,870 --> 00:57:21,000
Why was it not fun? Why was it boring?

1100
00:57:21,000 --> 00:57:25,440
It turns out I was bothered by the lines.

1101
00:57:25,440 --> 00:57:27,260
They kind of bothered me.

1102
00:57:27,260 --> 00:57:30,360
They might be entertaining temporarily.

1103
00:57:30,360 --> 00:57:34,030
But if it gets repeated, it might get boring.

1104
00:57:34,030 --> 00:57:39,900
I think that's what bored me a little.

1105
00:57:39,900 --> 00:57:41,670
Thank you.

1106
00:57:41,670 --> 00:57:43,650
He pressed the button.

1107
00:57:43,650 --> 00:57:47,250
This is unpredictable, too. It might flip.

1108
00:57:47,250 --> 00:57:50,130
[Judging ended]

1109
00:57:50,130 --> 00:57:55,740
A death match between
Directors Jeong Joo and Han Sang Il.

1110
00:57:55,740 --> 00:58:00,770
We are awaiting the final result that
includes the Five Stars' votes.

1111
00:58:00,770 --> 00:58:03,040
How do you two feel right now?

1112
00:58:03,040 --> 00:58:06,530
There is a bit of a gap between you.

1113
00:58:06,530 --> 00:58:09,980
But the result flipped in the last round.

1114
00:58:09,980 --> 00:58:13,290
Even one vote can change things.

1115
00:58:13,290 --> 00:58:16,400
Ten extra votes will do a lot.

1116
00:58:16,400 --> 00:58:20,170
The difference is not so big.

1117
00:58:20,170 --> 00:58:24,680
I'm curious what Jeong Joo
thought of Han Sang Il's work.

1118
00:58:24,680 --> 00:58:27,290
I have a lot more to learn from him.

1119
00:58:27,900 --> 00:58:31,130
He became a lot more modest.

1120
00:58:31,130 --> 00:58:34,200
The dynamic suddenly changed.

1121
00:58:34,200 --> 00:58:36,360
- All right.
- It was fun.

1122
00:58:37,180 --> 00:58:40,660
We are all aware of this rule.

1123
00:58:40,660 --> 00:58:43,100
This is before adding Five Stars' votes.

1124
00:58:43,100 --> 00:58:45,900
The result can easily change.

1125
00:58:45,900 --> 00:58:48,370
A battle between friends who turned enemies

1126
00:58:48,370 --> 00:58:50,810
High-quality filmmaker, Jeong Joo.

1127
00:58:50,810 --> 00:58:53,590
The master of absurd B-movies, Han Sang Il.

1128
00:58:53,590 --> 00:58:56,770
In this battle between two polar opposites,

1129
00:58:56,770 --> 00:59:00,240
who will end up being the winner?

1130
00:59:00,240 --> 00:59:02,140
Let's check the result.

1131
00:59:02,140 --> 00:59:04,250
[Result announcement]

1132
00:59:04,250 --> 00:59:06,370
[Drum roll]

1133
00:59:06,370 --> 00:59:08,240
[Nervous]

1134
00:59:08,240 --> 00:59:10,550
I was ahead in the viewer's vote,

1135
00:59:10,550 --> 00:59:13,740
but things might change
based on the judge's taste.

1136
00:59:13,740 --> 00:59:16,550
The anxiety overwhelmed me.

1137
00:59:17,750 --> 00:59:21,610
My film crew reacted very positively.

1138
00:59:21,610 --> 00:59:23,750
I think I might win.

1139
00:59:23,750 --> 00:59:25,240
I totally can.

1140
00:59:25,840 --> 00:59:29,900
Did the result change?

1141
00:59:29,900 --> 00:59:31,700
Please reveal.

1142
00:59:35,430 --> 00:59:36,570
[A huge difference]

1143
00:59:36,570 --> 00:59:41,410
The winner of this battle is
Director Han Sang Il.

1144
00:59:41,410 --> 00:59:44,620
28 versus 67 stop counts.

1145
00:59:44,620 --> 00:59:46,610
Director Han Sang Il is
advancing to the next round.

1146
00:59:46,610 --> 00:59:47,960
Congratulations.

1147
00:59:47,960 --> 00:59:51,890
Unfortunately, Director Jeong Joo lost.
How do you feel?

1148
00:59:51,890 --> 00:59:54,220
I don't think it was unfortunate.

1149
00:59:54,220 --> 00:59:56,330
I think I lost fair and square.

1150
00:59:56,330 --> 00:59:58,370
You are admitting that you lost.

1151
00:59:58,370 --> 00:59:59,970
I totally accept the result.

1152
00:59:59,970 --> 01:00:01,810
I really enjoyed his work.

1153
01:00:01,810 --> 01:00:04,210
How do you feel, Director Han Sang Il?

1154
01:00:04,210 --> 01:00:07,750
I'm glad I have something to say
to my wife later at home.

1155
01:00:07,750 --> 01:00:09,030
Love you, Honey.

1156
01:00:09,030 --> 01:00:10,520
[Clap, clap, clap]

1157
01:00:10,520 --> 01:00:12,830
I appreciate your hard work. Thank you.

1158
01:00:12,830 --> 01:00:14,710
Thank you.

1159
01:00:14,710 --> 01:00:17,370
[The death match helped them grow]

1160
01:00:18,440 --> 01:00:22,530
A battle of pride, a 1:1 death match.

1161
01:00:22,530 --> 01:00:27,360
The next round will be a battle of genre films.

1162
01:00:28,060 --> 01:00:30,190
He started out as an actor,

1163
01:00:30,190 --> 01:00:32,920
but he perfectly transitioned into a director.

1164
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:34,180
Director Lee Joo Seung.

1165
01:00:34,180 --> 01:00:37,070
And this person boasts 600 million viewers.

1166
01:00:37,070 --> 01:00:40,130
She's the directors' biggest threat.

1167
01:00:40,130 --> 01:00:42,450
Director Han Soo Ji, please come forward.

1168
01:00:42,450 --> 01:00:43,710
I remember. I remember.

1169
01:00:43,710 --> 01:00:45,560
I thought she was a potential winner.

1170
01:00:45,560 --> 01:00:48,200
[Potential winner vs. Rising dark horse]

1171
01:00:48,200 --> 01:00:51,410
[Highly anticipated]

1172
01:00:51,410 --> 01:00:55,250
[Han Soo Ji's "Snakes and Ladders"]

1173
01:00:56,790 --> 01:00:59,220
[A blockbuster teaser created with AI]

1174
01:00:59,670 --> 01:01:03,230
[And a powerful cameo
appearance from Shin Ye Eun]

1175
01:01:04,200 --> 01:01:08,480
You survived cleanly
with five stops. Congratulations.

1176
01:01:08,480 --> 01:01:10,110
Thank you.

1177
01:01:10,110 --> 01:01:12,520
I can sum this up in one word. Dopamine.

1178
01:01:12,520 --> 01:01:14,950
I think this is the best one.

1179
01:01:14,950 --> 01:01:17,750
That was the best. I lost. I totally lost.

1180
01:01:17,750 --> 01:01:21,510
Hello, I'm actor Lee Joo Seung.

1181
01:01:21,510 --> 01:01:26,200
I've thought a lot about how the
genre could work in a short form.

1182
01:01:26,200 --> 01:01:29,360
[He even appeared as the lead actor]

1183
01:01:29,700 --> 01:01:33,420
[He created suspense with his delicate acting]

1184
01:01:34,060 --> 01:01:36,520
[But the stop count skyrocketed
from the beginning]

1185
01:01:36,920 --> 01:01:41,680
With 23 stops, you get a chance to survive.

1186
01:01:41,680 --> 01:01:44,200
The number spiked in a certain scene.

1187
01:01:44,200 --> 01:01:46,180
I pressed the button.

1188
01:01:46,180 --> 01:01:49,420
The reason is that his approach was too literal.

1189
01:01:49,420 --> 01:01:52,260
I didn't care if Lee Joo Seung
directed it or not.

1190
01:01:52,260 --> 01:01:55,770
I can show in the actual series later.

1191
01:01:55,770 --> 01:01:57,930
I didn't feel hurt or anything.

1192
01:01:58,660 --> 01:02:00,960
[Han Soo Ji vs. Lee Joo Seung]

1193
01:02:00,960 --> 01:02:02,200
How powerful.

1194
01:02:02,200 --> 01:02:04,880
Genre films. I love it.

1195
01:02:04,880 --> 01:02:08,030
The colors are totally the opposite.

1196
01:02:08,030 --> 01:02:10,490
The thumbnails became more powerful.

1197
01:02:10,490 --> 01:02:11,960
I have no thoughts in my head.

1198
01:02:11,960 --> 01:02:14,290
- I don't feel nervous.
- I'm nervous.

1199
01:02:14,290 --> 01:02:16,600
[They have opposite energies,
just like their thumbnails]

1200
01:02:17,090 --> 01:02:19,360
[Confidence? Given up? He's calm for some reason]

1201
01:02:19,400 --> 01:02:22,800
By the way, it changed, right?

1202
01:02:22,800 --> 01:02:29,080
Director Lee Joo Seung's was called
"Ku...kuek..." or something like that.

1203
01:02:29,080 --> 01:02:32,370
- "Kuekkuku."
- Right, right.

1204
01:02:32,370 --> 01:02:33,910
He changed it.

1205
01:02:33,910 --> 01:02:37,300
- Welcome, Directors.
- Welcome.

1206
01:02:39,920 --> 01:02:44,850
Director Lee Joo Seung and
Director Han Soo Ji are here.

1207
01:02:44,850 --> 01:02:46,830
Before we start,

1208
01:02:46,830 --> 01:02:49,230
please say a word to each other.

1209
01:02:49,230 --> 01:02:52,080
"Snakes and Ladders." I love it.

1210
01:02:52,080 --> 01:02:53,590
I'll be looking forward to it.

1211
01:02:53,590 --> 01:02:55,200
[He doesn't want to say too much]

1212
01:02:55,200 --> 01:02:58,130
When I worked with Director Lee Yoo Jin,

1213
01:02:58,130 --> 01:03:02,410
I realized how busy actor-directors are.

1214
01:03:02,410 --> 01:03:07,660
I'm hoping he was busy with other projects.

1215
01:03:07,660 --> 01:03:11,880
That's the reason you chose him.

1216
01:03:11,880 --> 01:03:13,680
I went all in.

1217
01:03:15,060 --> 01:03:17,760
He canceled all of his schedule.

1218
01:03:17,760 --> 01:03:19,830
He only focused on this.

1219
01:03:19,830 --> 01:03:22,190
Why did he do that?

1220
01:03:22,190 --> 01:03:23,610
[Who will win the death match?]

1221
01:03:23,610 --> 01:03:26,460
Anyway, I'm in your care.

1222
01:03:27,050 --> 01:03:30,880
Director Lee Joo Seung is going first.

1223
01:03:32,460 --> 01:03:36,940
I noticed that earlier. Your title changed.

1224
01:03:36,940 --> 01:03:41,300
I got to understand short dramas
more as I went through the rounds.

1225
01:03:41,300 --> 01:03:47,860
I thought the titles that show the
genre and story were better.

1226
01:03:47,860 --> 01:03:50,110
That's why I changed the title.

1227
01:03:50,110 --> 01:03:53,230
I heard you didn't cast
a male lead this time, too.

1228
01:03:53,230 --> 01:03:55,040
Why did you act yourself?

1229
01:03:55,040 --> 01:04:00,300
I think I understand the script
better because I wrote it.

1230
01:04:00,300 --> 01:04:02,950
Instead of spending time
communicating with an actor,

1231
01:04:02,950 --> 01:04:08,050
I decided to act to be more efficient.

1232
01:04:08,050 --> 01:04:11,110
I tried imagining it just now.

1233
01:04:11,110 --> 01:04:14,540
When you act and direct at the same time,

1234
01:04:14,600 --> 01:04:17,800
do you say, "What did you say?
What did you say? Cut."

1235
01:04:17,800 --> 01:04:19,720
[She's right]

1236
01:04:19,720 --> 01:04:21,690
Hyung, I do that.

1237
01:04:21,700 --> 01:04:24,240
Or he could be doing this. "Ready, action.

1238
01:04:24,240 --> 01:04:26,600
What did you say? What did you say?"

1239
01:04:26,600 --> 01:04:29,720
- How was it? How did you do it?
- Everyone's curious.

1240
01:04:29,720 --> 01:04:30,960
How did you do it?

1241
01:04:30,960 --> 01:04:35,210
[Lee Joo Seung is absorbed
into the scene as an actor]

1242
01:04:35,870 --> 01:04:37,710
[And...]

1243
01:04:37,710 --> 01:04:38,980
Cut.

1244
01:04:38,980 --> 01:04:40,390
[That's how he did it]

1245
01:04:40,740 --> 01:04:43,520
[There are books all over the set as props]

1246
01:04:44,050 --> 01:04:47,120
[What role is he playing?]

1247
01:04:48,400 --> 01:04:52,010
[Novelist, Jeong Wu]

1248
01:04:52,780 --> 01:04:57,060
"A scientist quietly approaches
the truth amidst endless failure.

1249
01:04:57,060 --> 01:05:00,400
After thousands of repeated
failures and a long period

1250
01:05:00,400 --> 01:05:03,860
of boredom, a discovery finally comes to you."

1251
01:05:03,860 --> 01:05:05,980
This has great quotes.

1252
01:05:05,980 --> 01:05:07,950
[He's basically an author now]

1253
01:05:08,510 --> 01:05:10,310
[Tell us about your series]

1254
01:05:10,310 --> 01:05:14,710
I'm a former best-selling author
who lives on the first floor.

1255
01:05:14,710 --> 01:05:16,350
He doesn't have a follow-up book.

1256
01:05:16,350 --> 01:05:18,860
His career is basically gone.

1257
01:05:18,860 --> 01:05:23,480
While he's basically given up,
a murderer moves in upstairs.

1258
01:05:23,480 --> 01:05:25,600
He needs to report her to the police,

1259
01:05:25,600 --> 01:05:29,370
but he gets so inspired by the things she says.

1260
01:05:29,370 --> 01:05:33,300
So, he stays up all night and submits
the synopsis to the publisher.

1261
01:05:33,300 --> 01:05:37,200
[The inspiring murderer]

1262
01:05:37,870 --> 01:05:41,660
I'm playing Yeo Jin in "The Murderer Upstairs."

1263
01:05:41,660 --> 01:05:44,070
I'm actress Yoon So Yi.

1264
01:05:44,070 --> 01:05:47,040
[The actress with 25 years
of experience is in a short drama]

1265
01:05:47,040 --> 01:05:50,720
I am playing a bit of a mysterious woman.

1266
01:05:50,720 --> 01:05:53,160
She moves into the building one day

1267
01:05:53,160 --> 01:05:56,010
and lurks around the novelist, Jeong Wu.

1268
01:05:56,010 --> 01:06:00,630
She keeps evoking strange
emotions and situations.

1269
01:06:00,630 --> 01:06:03,780
That's the type of role I'm playing.

1270
01:06:03,780 --> 01:06:06,560
Don't you have a question for me?

1271
01:06:08,850 --> 01:06:10,930
You don't mind me waiting inside, right?

1272
01:06:11,590 --> 01:06:15,820
[Two actors' amazing acting showdown]

1273
01:06:16,680 --> 01:06:18,720
I'm a little concerned that

1274
01:06:18,720 --> 01:06:20,900
Director Han's series is huge in its scale.

1275
01:06:20,900 --> 01:06:25,360
There is a snake, throwing of dice, and missions.

1276
01:06:25,360 --> 01:06:29,370
Actress Yoon So Yi and I talked about it nonstop.

1277
01:06:29,370 --> 01:06:32,530
I was like, "Sunbaenim, will you lose to a snake?

1278
01:06:32,530 --> 01:06:34,580
We won't lose to a snake.

1279
01:06:34,580 --> 01:06:36,140
We're humans."

1280
01:06:36,140 --> 01:06:38,940
We got into it by saying stuff like this.

1281
01:06:38,940 --> 01:06:41,240
That makes me feel confident.

1282
01:06:41,870 --> 01:06:46,110
I hope, wish, and pray that you win.

1283
01:06:46,110 --> 01:06:48,090
I'll be cheering for you.

1284
01:06:48,090 --> 01:06:49,570
Lee Joo Seung, fighting!

1285
01:06:49,570 --> 01:06:52,220
"The Murderer Upstairs," fighting!

1286
01:06:53,270 --> 01:06:55,560
Director Lee Joo Seung's short drama,

1287
01:06:55,560 --> 01:06:58,580
"The Murderer Upstairs."
What would you like us to focus on?

1288
01:06:58,580 --> 01:07:00,390
Since it's a thriller,

1289
01:07:00,390 --> 01:07:05,750
I hope you focus on the chemistry
and tension between the actors.

1290
01:07:05,750 --> 01:07:08,860
We'll get started. Play the video.

1291
01:07:08,860 --> 01:07:10,850
I'm nervous.

1292
01:07:12,310 --> 01:07:14,620
[The smile is gone]

1293
01:07:14,620 --> 01:07:18,350
I don't think people will be
that excited about mine.

1294
01:07:18,350 --> 01:07:23,920
Director Han's teaser for "Snakes and Ladders"
shocked everyone.

1295
01:07:23,920 --> 01:07:29,010
